channel.title: Latest News and News Headlines | Daily Telegraph

item.title: Volcano erupts on Spain’s Canary Islands
item.description: The Cumbre Vieja volcano erupted on Spain's Canary Islands Sunday, spewing out lava, ash and a huge column of smoke after days of increased seismic activity and forcing the evacuation of around 5,000 local people, authorities said.

item.title: Pro-Kremlin party on track for majority after crackdown
item.description: President Vladimir Putin's United Russia party was on track to win a strong majority in a parliamentary vote, results showed Sunday, after an election that followed an unprecedented crackdown on the opposition.

item.title: ‘Minimal detail’: The big Ashes issue for England
item.description: Veteran England fast bowler Stuart Broad says he would be “happy” to get on a plane to Australia adamant a team of “some description” will travel for this summer’s Ashes.

item.title: Victoria records 567 new local cases
item.description: Victoria has recorded 567 new locally acquired Covid-19 cases on Monday.

item.title: In-person Emmys return as Netflix eyes TV’s top prize with ‘The Crown’
item.description: Television's top stars will gather in person for the first time in two years at Sunday's Emmys, where Netflix is tipped to finally win the small screen's biggest prize for "The Crown."

item.title: Horror protest moment shown on video
item.description: Shocking video has emerged of police appearing to push over an older woman during the violent anti-lockdown protests in Melbourne over the weekend.

item.title: ScoMo’s approval lowest since bushfires
item.description: Australians are fed up with both sides of politics, showing little faith in either the Coalition or the Labor Party, the latest Newspoll has revealed.

item.title: Biden asks for early talks with Macron amid submarine row
item.description: US President Joe Biden has requested early talks with French President Emmanuel Macron, France said on Sunday, in an apparent effort to mend fences after a row over a submarines contract sparked rare tensions between the allies.

item.title: The restrictions Victoria won’t ease
item.description: Victoria’s much anticipated road map to freedom out of Covid-19 lockdown has finally been unveiled, with the state’s sixth shutdown to continue until 70 per cent of the population is fully vaccinated.

item.title: All the new rules in NSW from today
item.description: Residents in the 12 Local Government Areas of concern have woken to several restrictions easing in their areas including the same ‘picnic’ concession afforded to the rest of greater Sydney.
